xy clusters, and find the average rate in the high mass\n($10\\leq\\log\\mathrm{(M_{*}/M_{\\odot})} \\leq 11.25$) cluster galaxies to be\ncomparable to equivalent field mass galaxies, with an average difference of\n$1.3 \\pm 0.3$. Considering the full mass ranges of both samples, we measure a\ndecrease in the overall rate per unit mass in the clusters compared to the\nfield. Differences in the two samples rates could be caused by an excess of\nwhite dwarfs in clusters due to a different initial mass function, cluster\ngalaxy mergers re-igniting star formation, or a difference in metallicity\nbetween the two environments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Feb 2023 11:29:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-13"}
